-0-0-en/info.html|title=YESASIA: Desperate Housewives (DVD) (The Complete Eighth And Final Season) (Hong Kong Version)|publisher=[[YesAsia]]|date=October 12, 2012|accessdate=April 18, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=\"center\"| The Complete Collection\n| align=\"center\"| September 25, 2012\n| align=\"center\"| September 24, 2012\n| align=\"center\"| December 7, 2012\n| colspan=\"2\" {{n/a}}\n| align=\"center\"| 45\n| align=\"center\"| 180\n| align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"tvshowsondvd.com\">{{cite web |url=http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/news/Desperate-Housewives-Season-8-and-The-Complete-Collection/16910 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=May 26, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120518013602/http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/news/Desperate-Housewives-Season-8-and-The-Complete-Collection/16910 |archivedate=May 18, 2012  }}, ''TVShowsonDVD.com'', May 5, 2012</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yesasia.com/global/desperate-housewives-dvd-s1-s8-boxset-taiwan-version/1032048865-0-0-0-en/info.html|title=YESASIA: Desperate Housewives (DVD) (S1-S8 Boxset) (Taiwan Version)|publisher=[[YesAsia]]|date=December 7, 2012|accessdate=April 18, 2017}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Merchandise==\n===Games===\n[[Buena Vista Games]] released the [[life simulation game|life simulation]] [[computer game|computer]] [[video game]] ''[[Desperate Housewives: The Game (2006 video game)|Desperate Housewives: The Game]]'' on October 5, 2006 in North America, featuring an original storyline spanning 12 episodes.<ref>{{cite web|title=Desperate Housewives \u2013 The Game |url=http://buenavistagames.go.com/desperatehousewives/ |work=Beuna Vista Games |accessdate=September 20, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140110161639/http://buenavistagames.go.com/desperatehousewives/ |archivedate=January 10, 2014 |df= }}</ref> The game is set on Wisteria Lane, but the player does not play as any of the housewives, although they frequently appear. A couple of months later, [[Gameloft]] released a [[mobile game]] based on the series.<ref>[http://www.gameloft.com/product.php?product=187&product_name=Desperate+Housewives%99 Desperate Housewives Mobile Game Official Website]{{dead link|date=January 2012}}, Retrieved August 3, 2007</ref> \"The inspiration for Gameloft's take on ''Desperate Housewives'' comes from the most unlikely place, too\u2014the original [[Mario Party]] on the [[Nintendo 64]].\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Buchanan|first=Levi|title=Desperate Housewives Review|url=http://au.ign.com/articles/2007/01/29/desperate-housewives-review|work=[[IGN]]|accessdate=September 20, 2013|date=January 29, 2007}}</ref>\n\nIn 2007, British company Re:creation published ''Desperate Housewives Dirty Laundry Game'', a [[board game]] based on the third season of ''Desperate Housewives''.<ref>[http://www.recreationplc.com/Tradecat_2006/Trade%20Catalogue.pdf Re:Creation 2007 Product Catalogue, page 15]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070928002637/http://www.recreationplc.com/Tradecat_2006/Trade%20Catalogue.pdf |date=September 28, 2007 }} , Retrieved August 3, 2007 {{cite web|url=http://www.recreationplc.com/Tradecat_2006/Trade+Catalogue.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=October 24, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303222450/http://www.recreationplc.com/Tradecat_2006/Trade%2BCatalogue.pdf |archivedate=March 3, 2016  }}</ref> Players attempt to guess their opponents' secrets by answering [[trivia]] questions, while keeping clues to their own secrets concealed.\n\nIn June 2017, [[Megazebra]] released [[Desperate Housewives: The Game (2017)|Desperate Housewives: The Game]] on App Store and on Google Play. Play as new neighbor on Wisteria Lane.\n\n===Soundtrack and literature===\n[[File:Ms. magazine Cover - Spring 2005.jpg|thumbnail|left|''[[Ms. (magazine)|Ms.]]'''s ''Desperate Housewives'' issue, published in 2005]]\nIn September 2005, [[Hollywood Records]] released a [[soundtrack album]] distributed by [[Universal Music Group]], ''[[Music from and Inspired by Desperate Housewives]]'', featuring music inspired by the series, as well as sound clips taken from the first season of the series. The songs included have been described as promoting \"[[girl power]]\", and among the artists appearing\u2014all being female\u2014were [[LeAnn Rimes]], [[Gloria Estefan]] and [[Shania Twain]].<ref>[{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r787383|pure_url=yes}} Allmusic: Desperate Housewives], Retrieved August 3, 2007</ref> Controversially, no originally composed music from the series was included on the album.\n\nTwo books have been officially released within the ''Desperate Housewives'' franchise. In September 2005, ABC's sister company [[Hachette Books#Hyperion Books|Hyperion Books]] released ''Desperate Housewives: Behind Closed Doors'' ({{ISBN|978-1-4013-0826-1}}), a companion to the first season of the series, written by the production team behind the series.<ref>{{cite book|title=Desperate Housewives: Behind Closed Doors|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=nRaZ2FSgzJQC|accessdate=September 21, 2013|date=September 28, 2005|publisher=Hyperion Books|isbn=978-1-4013-0826-1}}</ref> One year later, in October 2006, Hyperion published ''The Desperate Housewives Cookbook \u2013 Juicy Dishes and Saucy Bits'' ({{ISBN|978-1-4013-0277-1}}).<ref>{{cite book|last1=Styler|first1=Christopher|last2=Tobis|first2=Scott S.|title=The Desperate Housewives Cookbook: Juicy Dishes and Saucy Bits|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LA5RAAAACAAJ|accessdate=September 21, 2013|date=September 26, 2006|publisher=Hyperion Books|isbn=978-1-4013-0277-1}}</ref> In addition, official [[wall calendar]]s, featuring shots taken from the series, were published by [[Andrews McMeel Publishing]] for 2006, 2007 and 2008.<ref>[http://www.andrewsmcmeel.com/products/?isbn=0740765884 Andrews McMeel Publishing: Desperate Housewives 2008 Wall Calendar] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070928122122/http://www.andrewsmcmeel.com/products/?isbn=0740765884 |date=September 28, 2007 }}, Retrieved August 5, 2007</ref>\n\nFour unauthorized books written from different points of view were released in 2006. ''Delicious Housewives, A Novel of Erotica'', by International best-selling author Tamarias Tyree ({{ISBN|978-0-930865-79-5}}), from RSVP Press, is an [[erotic]] [[parody]] of the series featuring the housewives' sexual misadventures which eventually lead them to an appearance on the ''[[Jerry Springer Show]]''.\n''Reading 'Desperate Housewives': Beyond the White Picket Fence'' ({{ISBN|978-1-84511-220-2}}), from [[I.B. Tauris]], is an academic look at the show by [[film studies]] lecturers Janet McCabe and Kim Akass.<ref>[http://www.ibtauris.com/ibtauris/display.asp?K=9781845112202&sf_01=CAUTHOR&st_01=Janet+McCabe&sf_02=CTITLE&sf_03=KEYWORD&sf_04=identifier&m=2&dc=4 I.B. Tauris: Reading \"Desperate Housewives\" \u2013 Beyond the White Picket Fence], Retrieved August 5, 2007 &nbsp;{{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070928130455/http://www.ibtauris.com/ibtauris/display.asp?K=9781845112202&sf_01=CAUTHOR&st_01=Janet+McCabe&sf_02=CTITLE&sf_03=KEYWORD&sf_04=identifier&m=2&dc=4 |date=September 28, 2007 }}</ref> ''Welcome to Wisteria Lane: On America's Favorite Desperate Housewives'' ({{ISBN|978-1-932100-79-2}}), published by [[BenBella Books]], consists of seventeen essays written from a [[feminist]] perspective.<ref>[http://66.84.52.211/cgi-bin/plugins/MivaEmpresas/miva?plugins/MivaMerchants/merchant.mvc+Screen=PROD&Store_Code=BB&Product_Code=WTWL&Category_Code=DHW BenBella Books: Welcome to Wisteria Lane: On America's Favorite Desperate Housewives] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927103834/http://66.84.52.211/cgi-bin/plugins/MivaEmpresas/miva?plugins%2FMivaMerchants%2Fmerchant.mvc+Screen=PROD&Store_Code=BB&Product_Code=WTWL&Category_Code=DHW |date=September 27, 2007 }}, Retrieved August 5, 2007</ref> In Chalice Press' ''Not-So-Desperate: Fantasy, Fact and Faith on Wisteria Lane'' ({{ISBN|0-8272-2513-X}}), author Shawnthea Monroe gives a [[Christianity|Christian]] interpretation of the series.<ref>[http://www.cbp21.com/ProductDetail.asp?ProductID=2706 Chalice Press: Not-so-desperate \u2013 Fantasy, Fact And Faith on Wisteria Lane] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070928051808/http://www.cbp21.com/ProductDetail.asp?ProductID=2706 |date=September 28, 2007 }}, Retrieved August 5, 2007</ref> Also, following the \"real life desperate housewives\" phenomenon, several books have been released dealing with life strategies for contemporary women.\n\n===Fashion dolls and fragrances===\nIn December 2006, it was announced that the characters of Susan, Lynette, Bree, Gabrielle and Edie were to be made into {{convert|16|in|cm}} tall [[fashion doll]]s, produced by [[Alexander Doll Company|Madame Alexander]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Finn|first=Natalie|title=Desperate Housewives Play Around|url=http://au.eonline.com/news/54074/desperate-housewives-play-around|accessdate=September 20, 2013|newspaper=[[E! Online]]|date=January 2, 2007}}</ref> In 2007, they were released in a limited edition of 300 pieces each.<ref>[http://www.madamealexander.com/fall_2007/product_cat.php/subid=7/index.html Madame Alexander Fall 2007 collection: Couture \u2013 Desperate Housewives], Retrieved August 5, 2008  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070627153545/http://www.madamealexander.com/fall_2007/product_cat.php/subid%3D7/index.html |date=June 27, 2007 }}</ref> A [[fragrance]] was also launched by [[Coty Inc.]] in 2006, titled ''Forbidden Fruit'', and was composed of [[orange blossom]], [[peach]], [[apple]], [[lily flower|lily]], [[wisteria]], [[jasmine]], [[ylang-ylang]], [[sandalwood]], [[tonka bean]], [[vanilla]] and [[cedar wood|cedar]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Elliott|first=Stuart|title=Woman of a Scent|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/12/18/business/media/18adco_column.html|accessdate=October 22, 2013|newspaper=The New York Times|date=December 18, 2006}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fragrantica.com/perfume/Coty/Desperate-Housewives-Forbidden-Fruit-2970.html|title=Desperate Housewives Forbbiden Fruit Coty for women|publisher=[[Coty Inc.]]|work=Fragrantica|date=2006|accessdate=April 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Desperate-Housewives-Forbidden-Women-3-4-Ounces/dp/B0012RWOB8|title=Amazon.com : Desperate Housewives Forbbiden Fruit By Coty For Women. Eau De Parfum Spray 3.4-Ounces|publisher=[[Coty Inc.]]|work=[[Amazon.com]]|date=2006|accessdate=April 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fragrancenet.com/perfume/coty/desperate-housewives-forbidden-fruit/eau-de-parfum#147971|title=Desperate Housewives Forbbiden Fruit Eau De Parfum for Women by Coty|publisher=Coty Inc.|work=FragranceNet.com Inc [US]|date=2006|accessdate=April 17, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170120191844/http://www.fragrancenet.com/perfume/coty/desperate-housewives-forbidden-fruit/eau-de-parfum#147971|archive-date=January 20, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> In August 2009, a collection of four fragrances by LR Health & Beauty Systems, each based on and titled after a ''Desperate Housewives'' lead character, was presented: Susan's fragrance is composed of [[orange blossom]], cedar, sandalwood and [[white musk]], Lynette's fragrance is composed of [[cardamom]], [[star jasmine]] and [[musk]], Bree's fragrance is composed of green apple, [[white jasmine]], [[raspberry]], lily, [[amber]] and vanilla, and Gabrielle's fragrance is composed of raspberry, [[pineapple]], [[rose]], [[patchouli]] and [[blackberries]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fragrantica.com/perfume/LR/Desperate-Housewives-Susan-6741.html|title=Desperate Housewives Susan LR for women|publisher=LR Health & Beauty Systems|work=Fragrantica|date=August 2009|accessdate=April 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fragrantica.com/perfume/LR/Desperate-Housewives-Lynette-6743.html|title=Desperate Housewives Lynette LR for women|publisher=LR Health & Beauty Systems|work=Fragrantica|date=August 2009|accessdate=April 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fragrantica.com/perfume/LR/Desperate-Housewives-Bree-6740.html|title=Desperate Housewives Bree LR for women|publisher=LR Health & Beauty Systems|work=Fragrantica|date=August 2009|accessdate=April 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fragrantica.com/perfume/LR/Desperate-Housewives-Gabrielle-6742.html|title=Desperate Housewives Gabrielle LR for women|publisher=LR Health & Beauty Systems|work=Fragrantica|date=August 2009|accessdate=April 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===''Another Desperate Housewife'' commercials===\nIn conjunction with season six, Marc Cherry was commissioned to write eight \"mini-episodes\" entitled ''Another Desperate Housewife''. The episodes were written after the previous season's extensive product placement proved unpopular with the fans. The mini-episodes were written to advertise mobile phone company Sprint and involve just three characters.<ref>{{cite news|last=Parpis|first=Eleftheria|title=The New Mini-Series|url=http://www.adweek.com/news/advertising-branding/new-mini-series-100645|accessdate=October 26, 2013|newspaper=[[Adweek]]|date=October 19, 2009}}</ref> The two main characters are Stephanie (played by [[Rebecca Staab]]) and Lance (played by [[David Chisum]]) who have moved into the former house of Edie Britt after her death. The third character, Elsa, was Stephanie's friend. It is eventually revealed that Lance and Elsa have been having an affair. Stephanie finds out and tells Lance to break it off. Elsa suggests killing Stephanie, but Lance gets a text message indicating he's seeing another woman and a furious Elsa shoots him. In truth, Stephanie had sent the message herself. The final mini-episode has Elsa being arrested and Stephanie attracted to a handsome policeman at the scene. Each episode ends with a Mary Alice-like narration saying things such as \"This is suspicion on the Now Network\" or \"This is betrayal on the Now Network.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Nakashima |first=Ryan |last2=Yao |first2=Deborah |title=Dramatized ads weave plot lines around product |url=http://news.theage.com.au/breaking-news-technology/dramatized-ads-weave-plot-lines-around-product-20091001-gcwv.html |accessdate=October 26, 2013 |newspaper=[[The Age]] |date=October 1, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029194102/http://news.theage.com.au/breaking-news-technology/dramatized-ads-weave-plot-lines-around-product-20091001-gcwv.html |archivedate=October 29, 2013 |df= }}</ref>\n\n===Ask ''Desperate Housewives''===\nFor the sixth season of the series, ABC created \"Ask ''Desperate Housewives''\" to promote their website [[abc.go.com]]. It was presented and sponsored by [[Sprint Corporation|Sprint]], and it was hosted by series creator, Marc Cherry. In each special, Marc Cherry and an actress/actor of the series would answer questions that fans submitted to abc.go.com.\n\n==Adaptions==\nOn February 26, 2007, [[The Walt Disney Company]] announced that four South American versions of the show were about to begin production: one for Argentina, one for Colombia, one for Ecuador and one for Brazil.<ref>{{cite news|title='Housewives' going global|url=https://variety.com/2006/scene/vpage/housewives-going-global-1117939263/|accessdate=September 20, 2013|newspaper=Variety|date=March 5, 2006}}</ref> Later on, the Colombian and Ecuadorean productions merged, leaving three [[Latin America]]n shows. The Argentine version, titled ''[[Amas de Casa Desesperadas (Argentine TV series)|Amas de Casa Desesperadas]]'', began being broadcast in 2006. The first year proved successful enough for a second season to begin production.<ref>[http://www.canal13.com.ar/micrositios/amas.resena.html Amas de casa desesperadas Official Canal 13 Website] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070610041037/http://www.canal13.com.ar/micrositios/amas.resena.html |date=June 10, 2007 }} , Retrieved August 3, 2007</ref> The first season of the version for Colombia ([[RCN TV]]) and Ecuador ([[Teleamazonas]]), also titled ''[[Amas de Casa Desesperadas (Colombian\u2013Ecuadorian TV series)|Amas de Casa Desesperadas]]'', began being broadcast in Ecuador in May 2007, and was broadcast five days a week.<ref>[http://www.teleamazonas.com/amasdecasa.htm Amas de casa desesperadas Official Teleamazonas Website] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070716232635/http://www.teleamazonas.com/amasdecasa.htm |date=July 16, 2007 }} , Retrieved August 3, 2007</ref> In addition, the second American version was developed for the [[Spanish-language]] television network [[Univision]]. Just as the two previous Spanish versions, it was titled ''[[Amas de Casa Desesperadas (U.S. TV series)|Amas de Casa Desesperadas]]'', and the production began in July 2007.<ref>{{cite news|title=Univision gets Spanish 'Housewives'|url=https://variety.com/2007/scene/news/univision-gets-spanish-housewives-1117964896/|accessdate=September 20, 2013|newspaper=Variety|date=May 14, 2007|author=Anna Marie de la Fuente}}</ref> The Brazilian version, ''[[:pt:Donas de Casa Desesperadas (s\u00e9rie brasileira)|Donas de Casa Desesperadas]]'' began being broadcast on [[RedeTV!]] in 2008.<ref>[http://www.redetv.com.br/siteredetv/grupos/series/donasdecasadesesperadas/ Donas de Casa Desesperadas Official RedeTV Website], Retrieved August 3, 2007  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071201011406/http://www.redetv.com.br/siteredetv/grupos/series/donasdecasadesesperadas/ |date=December 1, 2007 }}</ref> The Turkish version titled ''[[Umutsuz Ev Kad\u0131nlar\u0131]]'' aired on [[Kanal D]] in Turkey from 2011 until 2013 and on [[Fox (Turkey)|FOX Turkey]] from 2013 until 2014.<ref>{{cite web|author=Do You Know Turkey |url=http://www.doyouknowturkey.com/new-tv-series-turkish-desperate-housewives/ |title=New Tv Series: Turkish Desperate Housewives |publisher=Do You Know Turkey |date=October 20, 2011 |accessdate=June 16, 2013}}</ref> In fall 2013, the [[Disney Media Distribution]] and the Nigerian television network EbonyLife TV announced that they were producing an African version of ''Desperate Housewives''. The series, titled ''[[Desperate Housewives Africa]]'', was scheduled to premiere in summer 2014 on EbonyLife TV. However, it aired its only season during 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ebonylifetv.com/desperate-housewives-africa/|title=Desperate Housewives Africa|publisher=EbonyLife TV|accessdate=April 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Region(s)\n! scope=\"col\"| Release\n! scope=\"col\"| Network(s)\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" align=\"center\"| ''[[Amas de Casa Desesperadas (Argentine TV series)|Amas de Casa Desesperadas]]''\n| align=\"center\"| Argentina\n| align=\"center\"| 2006\u201307\n| align=\"center\"| [[Canal 13 (Argentina)|Canal 13]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" align=\"center\"| ''[[Amas de Casa Desesperadas (Colombian\u2013Ecuadorian TV series)|Amas de Casa Desesperadas]]''\n| align=\"center\"| {{flatlist|\n* Colombia\n* Ecuador\n}}\n| align=\"center\"| 2007\n| align=\"center\"| {{flatlist|\n* [[RCN TV]] {{small|(Colombia)}}\n* [[Teleamazonas]] {{small|(Ecuador)}}\n}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" align=\"center\"| ''[[Amas de Casa Desesperadas (U.S. TV series)|Amas de Casa Desesperadas]]''\n| align=\"center\"| United States\n| align=\"center\"| 2008\n| align=\"center\"| [[Univision]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" align=\"center\"| ''[[:pt:Donas de Casa Desesperadas (s\u00e9rie brasileira)|Donas de Casa Desesperadas]]''\n| align=\"center\"| Brazil\n| align=\"center\"| 2007\u201308\n| align=\"center\"| [[RedeTV!]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" align=\"center\"| ''[[Umutsuz Ev Kad\u0131nlar\u0131]]''\n| align=\"center\"| Turkey\n| align=\"center\"| 2011\u201314\n| align=\"center\"| {{flatlist|\n* [[Kanal D]] {{small|(2011\u201313)}}\n* [[Fox (Turkey)|FOX Turkey]] {{small|(2013\u201314)}}\n}}\n|-\n! sc